comment.body:
`validateProperties` sets `propertyConfiguration.experiment = { mode: 'startup' }` whenever the `onExP` tag is present, which will overwrite any `experiment` object already contributed by an extension (including `mode: 'auto'` or a custom `name`). Consider only applying this fallback when `propertyConfiguration.experiment` is currently undefined, so extension-provided experiment metadata is preserved.
```suggestion
					if (isUndefined(propertyConfiguration.experiment)) {
						propertyConfiguration.experiment = {
							mode: 'startup'
						};
					}
```

